	 Work experience in the speciality -&nbsp;#FROM_1970#. Teaching experience at the Chair of Obstetrics and Gynecology of the Pavlov Saint-Petersburg State Medical University - 35 years.
</p>
<ul>
	<li>Prof. Vladislav Korsak has been President of the Russian Association of Human Reproduction since 1995. </li>
	<li>He has been a member of the EIM Consortium, European Society of Human Reproduction and Embryology (ESHRE) since 2000 and a member of the Steering Committee of EIM Consortium, ESHRE, since 2009. </li>
	<li>Prof. Korsak represents the Russian Federation in the Asia Pacific Initiative on Reproduction (ASPIRE), he regularly takes part, as an invited speaker and chair of the sessions, in the events of the International Federation of Fertility Societies (IFFS), the Ukranian Association of Reproductive Medicine (UARM), and the Kazakhstan Association of Reproductive Medicine (КАRМ), Honoured Member of the KARM. </li>
	<li>Prof. Korsak is a member of editorial board of Reproduction Problems journal. </li>
	<li>He is a member of the Working Group on Reproductive Health of the Expert Healthcare Council at the Committtee of the Federation Council on Social Policy and Healthcare, Federal Assembly of the Russian Federation. </li>
	<li>In different years of his prfessional career, Prof. Korsak was a member of the WG of the State Duma Comiittee on Healthcare and WG on Reproductive Technologies of the Russian Ministry of Health. </li>
</ul>
<p>
	 In recent years, his main areas of research have been infertility treatment and assisted reproductive technologies. Prof. Korsak is an author of more than 200 publications including 5 methodological recommendations, 3 books and 9 testing software programs on Obstetrics and Gynecology.
